Refer to the figure <image 1>, Which term refers to the end of the story, or the very last event that takes place?

A. Resolution
B. Exposition
C. Conflict
D. Rising Action

The term that refers to the end of the story, or the very last event that takes place, is:

A. Resolution

The phrase "And they lived happily ever after" typically signifies the resolution of a story, indicating that all conflicts have been resolved and the story has reached its conclusion.
